Prismati Player			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Prismati Player],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:Andoran	DESC:You’ve grown up playing the confusing game of prismati and throw stones with accuracy and ease. You gain a +1 trait bonus on attack rolls with fistsized rocks or similarly shaped objects, and a +1 trait bonus on concentration checks.	BONUS:CONCENTRATION|ALLSPELLS|1|TYPE=Trait		SOURCEPAGE:p.7
Kobolds Neighbor		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Kobolds Neighbor],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:Andoran	DESC:You grew up in wilderness where kobolds make their homes. You learned early on how to find traps before they find you, how to disable them, and when you should just walk away. You gain a +2 trait bonus to Perception checks to discover traps and a +1 trait bonus to Disable Device checks.	BONUS:SKILL|Disable Device|1|TYPE=Trait		SOURCEPAGE:p.9
Carpenden Lobber		NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Carpenden Lobber],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:Andoran	DESC:Your regular participation in the moonmelon festival has made you wickedly effective at hurling harmless objects. You gain a +2 trait bonus on attack rolls when throwing items that do not deal normal hit point damage (such as weapons that deal nonlethal damage or items such as tanglefoot bags and thunderstones).	SOURCEPAGE:p.19
Carpenden Roof Runner	NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Carpenden Roof Runner],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]	PREREGION:Andoran	DESC:Your childhood playing atop Carpenden’s buildings has given you a remarkable head for heights. You gain a +2 trait bonus on Acrobatics checks made when you are at least 20 feet above the ground.																							SOURCEPAGE:p.19
Oregent Desperation		NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Oregent Desperation],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]	PREREGION:Andoran	DESC:Your instinct to survive easily overpowers your intellect, and you consider this a more than fair trade. Once per day you can improve your condition from dying to disabled by taking 4 points of Intelligence damage.																		SOURCEPAGE:p.20
Oregent Timing			NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Oregent Timing],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:Andoran	DESC:After years of soulnumbing obedience to the schedules of others, you find synchronizing your actions with an ally second nature. Once per day when you take a readied action in combat, you gain a +3 trait bonus on the d20 roll for that action if it was triggered by an ally’s action.	SOURCEPAGE:p.20
Oregent Vandal			NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Oregent Vandal],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait]		PREREGION:Andoran	DESC:You find it quite easy to apply your carefully honed instincts for building and repairing to destruction instead. You gain a +2 trait bonus on damage rolls made against targets with hardness. This bonus does not apply to attacks that ignore hardness.									SOURCEPAGE:p.20

